Business Problem

In Oracle Fusion PPM, project and task details live across multiple tables. Reporting on A client a project becomes a little hard to connect via SQL because the client relationship is not stored directly on the project — it is resolved through the billing contract chain:
Project → Contract Project Link → Contract Line → Billing Plan → Customer Account → Party (Client Name)

This query solves both problems in a single, reusable SQL that also supports dynamic filtering by project name or a last-update date range — making it suitable for scheduled BIP reports and on-demand extracts.

Parameters

Parameter:P_PROJECT_NAMEVARCHAR2 is the project name. When supplied, date range is ignored.:P_START_DATEVARCHAR2 (YYYY-MM-DD) last-update date window for projects or tasks.:P_END_DATEVARCHAR2 (YYYY-MM-DD) last-update date window for projects or tasks.

Note: At least one parameter must be supplied. If both P_PROJECT_NAME and the date range are NULL, the query returns no rows (by design, to prevent unbounded full-table scans in production).

SELECT 
    proj.segment1                          AS project_number,
    proj_tl.name                           AS project_name,
    proj.project_status_code               AS project_status,
    projt.enable_billing_flag              AS billable_flag,
    TRIM(proj.start_date)                  AS start_date,
    TRIM(proj.completion_date)             AS end_date,
    hou.name                               AS client,
    proj.attribute1                        AS division,
    proj.attribute2                        AS product,
    task_tl.name                           AS task_name,
    task.element_number                    AS task_number,
    TRIM(task.start_date)                  AS task_start_date,
    TRIM(task.completion_date)             AS task_end_date,
    task.billable_flag                     AS task_billable_status,
    hou.name                               AS business_unit,
    (SELECT haotl.name
       FROM hr_organization_units_f_tl haotl
      WHERE haotl.organization_id = proj.project_unit_id
        AND haotl.language        = USERENV('LANG')
        AND ROWNUM = 1)                    AS project_unit
FROM
    pjf_projects_all_b      proj,
    pjf_project_types_b     projt,
    pjf_projects_all_tl     proj_tl,
    pjf_proj_elements_b     task,
    pjf_proj_elements_tl    task_tl,
    hr_operating_units      hou,
    (SELECT
         cpl.project_id,
         kl.bill_plan_id,
         kl.major_version,
         ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
             PARTITION BY cpl.project_id
             ORDER BY kh.start_date DESC, cpl.contract_id DESC
         ) AS rn
     FROM
         pjb_cntrct_proj_links cpl,
         pjb_bill_plans_b      bp,
         okc_k_headers_all_b   kh,
         okc_k_lines_b         kl
     WHERE cpl.active_flag    = 'Y'
       AND kh.id              = cpl.contract_id
       AND kh.major_version   = cpl.major_version
       AND kh.template_yn     = 'N'
       AND kl.id              = cpl.contract_line_id
       AND kl.major_version   = cpl.major_version
       AND kl.version_type   IN ('A','C')
       AND kl.sts_code       IN ('ACTIVE','EXPIRED','HOLD','CLOSED')
       AND bp.bill_plan_id    = kl.bill_plan_id
       AND bp.major_version   = kl.major_version
    )                       cpl_ranked,
    pjb_bill_plans_b        bp,
    hz_cust_accounts        hca,
    hz_parties              hp
WHERE

        proj.project_type_id      = projt.project_type_id
    AND proj.project_id           = proj_tl.project_id
    AND proj_tl.language          = USERENV('LANG')
    AND proj.org_id               = hou.organization_id
    AND task.project_id           = proj.project_id
    AND task.element_type         = 'FINANCIAL'
    AND task.object_type          = 'PJF_TASKS'
    AND task.project_id           = task_tl.project_id
    AND task.proj_element_id      = task_tl.proj_element_id
    AND task_tl.language          = USERENV('LANG')

    AND cpl_ranked.project_id  = proj.project_id(+)
    AND cpl_ranked.rn          = 1
    AND bp.bill_plan_id        = cpl_ranked.bill_plan_id(+)
    AND bp.major_version       = cpl_ranked.major_version(+)
    AND hca.cust_account_id    = bp.bill_to_cust_acct_id(+)
    AND hp.party_id            = hca.party_id(+)
    AND hou.name IN ('BU1','BU2')
    AND proj.clin_linked_code IS NOT NULL
    AND (
            (:P_PROJECT_NAME IS NOT NULL AND proj_tl.name = :P_PROJECT_NAME)
         OR (:P_START_DATE   IS NOT NULL AND :P_END_DATE IS NOT NULL
             AND (   proj.last_update_date BETWEEN TO_DATE(:P_START_DATE,'YYYY-MM-DD')
                                               AND TO_DATE(:P_END_DATE,  'YYYY-MM-DD')
                  OR task.last_update_date BETWEEN TO_DATE(:P_START_DATE,'YYYY-MM-DD')
                                               AND TO_DATE(:P_END_DATE,  'YYYY-MM-DD'))));


Important tables:

PJF_PROJECTS_ALL_B → Project header
PJF_PROJ_ELEMENTS_B → Tasks/WBS
PJB_CNTRCT_PROJ_LINKS → Project-contract relationship
OKC_K_HEADERS_ALL_B → Contract headers
OKC_K_LINES_B → Contract lines
PJB_BILL_PLANS_B → Billing plans
HZ_CUST_ACCOUNTS → Customer accounts
HZ_PARTIES → Customer names

In Fusion PPM, the client-to-project relationship is indirect — always resolved through the contract billing chain, not a direct FK on the project table.
The _TL (translation) tables in Fusion always require a language filter — omitting it produces one row per installed language.
